Question: How to read a file in Java line by line?
Please using this api: BufferedReader.readLine.
Answer:<<<api>>>: BufferedReader.readLine
<<<code>>>: BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
reader.close();
<<<explanation>>>: The readLine() method of the BufferedReader class reads a line of text. A line is considered to be terminated by any one of a line feed ('\n'), a carriage return ('\r'), or a carriage return followed immediately by a line feed.
Question: How to convert a string to an integer in Java?
Please using this api: Integer.parseInt.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Integer.parseInt
<<<code>>>: String str = "123";
int num = Integer.parseInt(str);
<<<explanation>>>: The parseInt() method of the Integer class parses the string argument as a signed decimal integer. The characters in the string must all be decimal digits, except that the first character may be an ASCII minus sign '-' to indicate a negative value. The resulting integer value is returned.
Question: How to convert a string to a double in Java?
Please using this api: Double.parseDouble.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Double.parseDouble
<<<code>>>: String str = "123.45";
double num = Double.parseDouble(str);
<<<explanation>>>: The parseDouble() method of the Double class parses the string argument as a double. The resulting double value is returned.
Question: How to convert a string to a boolean in Java?
Please using this api: Boolean.parseBoolean.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Boolean.parseBoolean
<<<code>>>: String str = "true";
boolean bool = Boolean.parseBoolean(str);
<<<explanation>>>: The parseBoolean() method of the Boolean class parses the string argument as a boolean. The string is considered to be a case-insensitive representation of a Boolean value. If the string is "true", "yes", "y", "on", or "1", the result is true. If the string is "false", "no", "n", "off", or "0", the result is false. If the string is not one of these, then the method throws an IllegalArgumentException.
